        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46075",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've attached a patch which reproduces this issue.  When creating checkboxes with array notation (ie: foo[]), all elements end up with id=\"foo\", which isn't good HTML.\n\nAs far as I can see, there are three options for fixing this issue:\n# Empty the id attribute when array notation is detected (as OP suggested)\n# Require that the ID element be specified by the user when calling the helper (breaks BC)\n# Use the value as part of the id attribute \n\nI've attached a patch which implements the latter - use the value as part of the id attribute. For instance, an array of three checkboxes would currently look something like this:\n{code}\n<input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"foo[]\" id=\"foo\" value=\"bar0\">\n<input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"foo[]\" id=\"foo\" value=\"bar1\">\n<input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"foo[]\" id=\"foo\" value=\"bar2\">\n{code}\nAfter applying my fix, the HTML would look like this:\n{code}\n<input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"foo[]\" id=\"foo-bar0\" value=\"bar0\">\n<input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"foo[]\" id=\"foo-bar1\" value=\"bar1\">\n<input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"foo[]\" id=\"foo-bar2\" value=\"bar2\">\n{code}\n\nThoughts?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-04-28T14:01:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-04-28T14:01:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46173",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Changing the way the id attribute is rendered will cause a backwards-compatibility break.  I've marked this issue as postponed to next major release. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-04-28T21:08:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-04-28T21:08:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48375",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "ZF provides Zend_View_Helper_FormMultiCheckbox for such an occasion, and it works exactly like you have proposed here (ie: append value to end of id to make it unique)\n\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.view.helpers.html#zend.view.helpers.initial\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-09T00:01:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-09T00:01:47.000+0000"
                }
            ]
